# 4. 正しい選択

Elementary School Shiho: ...
Classmate C's Voice: Right... But she promised ages ago that she'd come. Shouldn't this party take priority?
Classmate A's Voice: Yeah... But if it didn't sound like she was gonna budge...
Elementary School Shiho: (Maybe I should've gone instead...)
Elementary School Shiho: (But if I had, I wouldn't have finished my assignment...)
Father: Shiho, is that you?
Elementary School Shiho: Oh, Dad... Are you coming back from work?
Father: Yeah. I was just having a meeting with this band I've been looking after. They have a show coming up.
Father: Are you on your way home from school, Shiho? It's pretty late...
Elementary School Shiho: I was busy doing calligraphy today.
Father: Calligraphy?
Elementary School Shiho: Yeah, we were assigned to draw characters for class. The due date was today, so I had to stay back and finish mine.
Father: I see... So, did yours turn out the way you wanted?
Elementary School Shiho: Well...
Elementary School Shiho: What I turned in was probably the best one I've ever drawn...
Father: That's good.
Father: But you don't seem all that happy...
Elementary School Shiho: Huh...? I'm, uhh...
Father: It's okay. You can tell me what's wrong...
Father: I'm sure you'll feel a lot better after you get it off your chest.
Elementary School Shiho: Okay...
Elementary School Shiho: I was actually supposed to go to a classmate's birthday party today... But I decided not to go because I wanted to keep working on my calligraphy...
Elementary School Shiho: And my decision ended up hurting them.
Father: ...
Elementary School Shiho: I know I would've regretted turning in something I wasn't happy with.
Elementary School Shiho: But I also never meant to upset everyone...
Elementary School Shiho: Which is why I'm wondering if I should've gone to that party after all...
Father: I see. That's a tough pickle...
Father: Still, after deciding to stay back, you ended up producing your best piece of calligraphy today, right?
Father: I think you should be proud of that.
Elementary School Shiho: You think so...?
Father: Yes. However, I also understand your predicament...
Father: Getting to do what you want is important, but so is understanding how others feel.
Elementary School Shiho: Yeah...
Elementary School Shiho: (Did I make the right decision?)
Elementary School Shiho: (Ideally, I would've been able to work faster and still make it to the birthday party, but...)
Father: ...
Father: Shiho, why don't we go see another show together sometime?
Elementary School Shiho: A show? Sure, but where'd that come from...?
Father: There's a group of ladies that I want you to meet.
Father: Hearing their music might give you a hint as to how you should make those kinds of decisions going forward.
Elementary School Shiho: A hint...?
Father: Yeah. So, how about it...?
Elementary School Shiho: Yeah... Okay.
Elementary School Shiho: (I'm at a live house again... But it's never not exciting to be at one.)
Elementary School Shiho: (It being kinda dark is a part of it... But there's more to it than just that...)
Elementary School Shiho: (The sounds you sometimes hear when they're tuning and testing the instruments. The way you can sorta barely see what's going on. All of that...)
Elementary School Shiho: (I dunno why, but it always gets me really excited...)
Father: Over here, Shiho.
Elementary School Shiho: Huh? Wait, we're going backstage...? Am I allowed?
Father: Yeah, I already got permission. It's okay as long as you don't get in the way of the staff...
Elementary School Shiho: Okay...
Elementary School Shiho: (This is what it looks like backstage...? I had no idea...)
???: Oh, Mr. Hinomori, you made it!
Elementary School Shiho: ...!
Father: I thought this was my chance to say hi. You don't go on for a little while, right?
Girl Band Member A: Wow, thank you so much! Sumire's gonna be so stoked!
Girl Band Member A: Huh? That girl...
Elementary School Shiho: Oh...
Girl Band Member A: Is she your daughter...?!
Father: Yeah, her name's Shiho.
Father: Shiho, this is the leader of Iolite. They're the band I said I've been looking after, remember...?
Elementary School Shiho: Nice to meet you...
Iolite Member A: Whoa...! Y-Y-Y-Y-You're...
Elementary School Shiho: Me...?
Iolite Member A: You're soooo cute!
Iolite Member A: Everyone, listen! Big news! Mr. Hinomori brought over this really adorable girl to meet us! Apparently she's his daughter, Shiho!
Iolite Member B: Oh, hey, look at that. How old are you, sweetie?
Elementary School Shiho: Um... I'm ten.
Iolite Member A: Ten?! Wow, you're so calm and collected though.
Iolite Member B: Come to think of it, Mr. Hinomori, she looks just like you. I dunno if it's her eyes, but she looks like she means business just like her daddy. I bet she'll grow up to have a really cool look.
Iolite Member C: You think so? But she's so soft and cuddly. Just feel her cheeks. She's gonna turn out such a cutie.
Iolite Member A: Either way, she's a gorgeous girl! I can't get enough of her.
Elementary School Shiho: W-Wait... Hey, quit it...!
???: Oh, geez. What are you guys up to now?
Elementary School Shiho: Huh?
???: Give her some space, will you? Imagine having a bunch of strangers gang up on you like that. Wouldn't you feel terrified?
???: Sorry about that. They don't mean you any harm...
Elementary School Shiho: No, I...
Sumire: Oh, I'm Sumire Kuno. It's great to meet you. I'm the bassist for this band.
